The paper focuses on developing autonomous assistants for domestic tasks, specifically garment folding, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The proposed solution involves using deep learning models for garment localization and landmark detection, which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of memory and processing efficient solutions, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
